POV: You took a solo trip to Sweden to see Beyoncé in Club Renny and had the time of your life 🫶🏿🇸🇪

First off, let’s hear some commotion for the fit cause honestly I could’ve been a background dancer 🪩 Second, was it worth it? Absolutely and I’d do it again. I don’t know another artist putting on a show like this woman. Everything is just always done on the highest of levels with so much thought 😭 She does old and new songs including all of Renaissance album. The show was long too so you get your moneys worth. I took all the good pics of Bey on my digital camera and only have video on my phone and they’re like 4 minutes long each so I need to sort through everything. I also have commentary on where I believe is the best section to watch the show from which I’ll share 🙂tbh, just go see it. 

#beyonce #clubrenaissance #renaissanceworldtour #rwt #bey #beyhive #sweden #stockholm #friendsarena #queenbey

idk why people on Tik Tok keep asking me if I know she’s going to Houston 😒 do they not know how hard it was to get tickets in the states 🧐

#beyonce #sweden #stockholm #bey #rwt #renaissance #renaissanceworldtour #htx #queenbey #outfitinspo

I don’t have many regrets in life, but I’ll tell you this. Not sneaking my DSLR into this show is one of them 😭 I just didn’t want to risk having to go back to my air bnb or getting put out the show 😐

Before I went to Sweden, I was in Japan 🇯🇵 This means I was pretty much back and forth between 3 continents within 2 weeks. I’m honestly only posting this cause if I don’t post it, did it really happen? 

Tokyo is literally a clean New York. Like it’s so clean there. I also felt extremely safe. I’m being a poser in the first pic cause I didn’t take the train. I ran up an Uber tab instead🙃 Best ramen I’ve ever had was there and long story short I’ll be back ☝🏿

Sidenote: I wish I could clone myself so I can take actual good pics of myself when I go places. No tripod or selfies allowed ❌

#japan #tokyo #tokyonights #canonphotographer #travelphotography

POV: you went to a party by yourself and had a great time 🫶🏿

I usually do a lot of things by myself so I’m no stranger to this life. However, I don’t usually like going to parties alone so I pushed myself to do so and actually enjoyed it. I’ve been to @physicaltherapyhtx a few times before and like the atmosphere & music so that helped. I ran into people I knew and that helped too, but honestly I moved around freely and danced solo! 

We often say we enjoy our own company, but I want to make sure I’m not just saying it and actually feel that way. More solo adventures incoming 🩵

really groovy ☮️✌🏿

It finally happened. After over a decade of supporting my two favs, I got them in the same area at the same time for this iconic moment 😭 To the average person this is just a picture, but to me this is much more. I discovered Drake musically via Comeback Season and Cole via The Warm Up and they been stuck with me ever since. I remember flying to London in 2011 just to see them together as they were on tour together. I remember Drake telling me he was extending Club Paradise tour and that Cole was gonna be on it and my face lighting up. I remember flying all over to see Cole and him being confused on where I actually lived cause I was everywhere 😂 So many memories and believe me I remember them all. When I think of a lot of the best times in my life, it had something to do with these two. LOVE YOU BOTH ALWAYS 🫶🏿✨ Also, please note how big I’m smiling on the outside because that’s how I felt on the inside 😆

Will they ever give me flowers? Well, of course not. They don’t wanna have that talk cause it’s a sore spot 🥀
